## 2. Dark Mode

All colors must use semantic tokens from `elephant-ai/apps/web/src/index.css`. Semantic tokens automatically switch between light and dark mode via the `.dark` class.

### Verification Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded `bg-white` -- use `bg-card` or `bg-background`
- [ ] No hardcoded `text-black` -- use `text-foreground`
- [ ] No hardcoded `border-gray-*` -- use `border-border`
- [ ] No hardcoded hex colors or RGB values
- [ ] Status colors (emerald, amber, rose, blue) need dark mode consideration -- these Tailwind colors don't auto-adapt, so use them only for badges/status indicators where the contrast is acceptable in both modes
- [ ] SVG fills and strokes use `currentColor` or semantic tokens

### How to Verify

Check the component in Storybook with the theme switcher (toolbar dropdown). If any element becomes invisible, unreadable, or jarring in dark mode, fix it.

