## 3. State Completeness

Every component that displays data must handle all four states:

### Loading State

- Use `Skeleton` components from `@/components/ui/skeleton`
- Match the shape and size of the content being loaded
- Skeletons pulse (`animate-pulse`) to indicate activity
- Never show a blank screen while data loads

```
<Skeleton className="h-5 w-3/4" />   /* title-sized skeleton */
<Skeleton className="h-4 w-1/2" />   /* description-sized skeleton */
```

### Empty State

- Show a helpful message explaining why there's no data
- Include a primary action to resolve the empty state when possible
- Use an icon or illustration to make it feel intentional, not broken
- Center vertically and horizontally in the available space

### Error State

- Explain what went wrong in plain language (not technical error messages)
- Provide a clear recovery action ("Try again", "Refresh", "Go back")
- Use `text-destructive` for the error message
- Never show a raw error string from the API

### Disabled State

- Interactive elements use `opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed`
- Disabled buttons must not trigger actions
- If an entire section is disabled, explain why with a tooltip or message

